---
title: Cajun Spiced Roasted Vegetable Stew with Rice and Coriander Yoghurt
description: Spoon comfort into your bowl with our elevated riff on a beloved homestyle classic! Sweet potato, colourful peppers and red onion come together in a savoury and satisfying stew. Fluffy rice and a dollop of yoghurt served alongside make this the perfect midweek meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/cajun-spiced-roasted-vegetable-stew-2e6bb200-a5840da4.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/cajun-spiced-roasted-vegetable-stew-5f297fbf226ba26eee2f94cd-afc56cdf.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/cajun-spiced-roasted-vegetable-stew-5f297fbf226ba26eee2f94cd
author: Michael Steadman
nutrition:
  calories: 643 kcal
  fat: 5 g
  saturated fat: 1 g
  carbohydrates: 122 g
  sugar: 27 g
  protein: 23 g
  sodium: 3.4 g
  serving size: 907
course: main course
time required: 45 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: South American
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel!). Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm sized chunks. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into 1cm sized chunks. Pop the sweet potato, pepper and onion on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over some oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until tender and starting to char, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway.

Meanwhile, pour the @water{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, roughly chop the @coriander{1}(chopped) (stalks and all). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}. In a #small bowl{} combine the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} with half of the chopped coriander. Stir together and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on a medium high heat. When hot, add the red kidney beans, garlic, @smoked paprika{1} and @cajun spice mix{1}. Cook stirring frequently for ~{1%minute}.

> Add less Cajun spice if you don't like heat.

Add the @vegetable stock powder{1}, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1} and @water{100%ml}. Bring to a boil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn the heat down to a simmer and cook for ~{6-8%minutes} until slightly reduced. Add the roasted veggies once they are cooked, stir through the sauce and add a splash of water to loosen if you need to.

Season the sauce to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the remaining coriander into your rice and fluff with a #fork{}. Share the rice between your plates and top with the roasted vegetable stew. Serve with a dollop of coriander yogurt. Enjoy!